- How to: configure the maximum amount of shared memory on a Linux system
   cat /proc/sys/kernel/shmmax
   echo 335544320 > /proc/sys/kernel/shmmax

- How to: check memory usage of your process
   watch ps -C yorick -F

- How to: check System V IPC internal
   man ipcs

- How to: System V IPC reference and reading
   http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/System_V
   http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shared_memory
